  "detailedRequirements": "<p>Our challenge app uses the basic mean.io stack with added support for postgres. &nbsp; We have have the basic skeleton that allows a user to create a challenge. &nbsp;We would like to know add an auto save feature.</p>\n\n<p>To start this challenge checkout out the seed code from our serenity <a href=\"https://github.com/topcoderinc/serenity-core\">repo</a> https://github.com/topcoderinc/serenity-core. &nbsp;Please read the read which will give you instruction on how to connect to the default Deadwood databases and how to switch to a local copy. &nbsp; For this challenge you should connect to your own database so we don&rsquo;t get into database race conditions while in development.</p>\n\n<p>The goal of this challenge to to auto-save challenges from create or edit much like google docs do. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong><br />\n1. &nbsp;On the create and edit challenge listview create a toggle button at the top called auto save and which is default set to on.<br />\n2. &nbsp;Modify the form so the title of the challenge is &lsquo;untitled challenge&rsquo;<br />\n3. &nbsp;If any of the form data is filled out other than the title default value of &lsquo;untitled challenge&rsquo;, save the challenge to the database at an appropriate interval (you decide or make it configurable) or do it based on change.<br />\n4. &nbsp;Your solution should show the user when the save is taking place and give them anindication of when it was last save between the act of saving. &nbsp;<br />\n5. &nbsp;If you are keeping time please address any memory leakage<br />\n6. &nbsp;You should assume that more fields will be added to the form and an ideal solution will enable autosave of newly added fields with little effort.</p>\n\n<p>The nature of this challenge is very exploratory so consider the requirements are loose and we are hoping to learn what we can and can&rsquo;t do so we are open to any suggestions or deviations from requirements.</p>\n",
